Distribution and habitat .
Gallardoneris iberica
sp. nov.
was found in the Portuguese continental shelf at depths ranging from 18 to 180 m (cf.
Table 3
). The specimens inhabit mainly finer sediments with high content of fines, biogenic fraction and TOM (
Table 3
). The Galician shelf and the Gulf of Cรกdiz shelf (northwestern and southern Iberia ) present extensive mud patches being a continuity of the muddy areas recorded in the shelf off the rivers Minho and Guadiana (
Dias et al. 2002
;
Gonzalez et al. 2004
;
Martins et al. 2012
). These sediments seem to be preferred by this species and therefore it is expected to be found in those shelf areas.
